# Suggestion payload contract
Inferred values
Size and format

Derived out of:
DOI: `https://doi.org/{DOI}` -> `https://dataservices.gfz-potsdam.de/.../{ID}` -> `https://datapub.gfz.de/download/{ID}`

{DOI}: DOI of a dataset wihch will be pulled out of a database.
{ID}: Unknown website specified Identifier. 

## URL input contract

- The assistant may start with a DOI URL such as `https://doi.org/{DOI}`.
- DOI URLs are valid input, but they are not the final allowed-source URL.
- A DOI URL must first be resolved to its final landing page URL.
- The allowed-source check must happen after DOI resolution, not before.
- If the resolved landing page URL is not an allowed source, the resource must be skipped with a clear reason.

`https://dataservices.gfz-potsdam.de/.../{ID}`:
- Need to find download link leading to webiste specific link.
(`https://datapub.gfz.de/download/{ID}`)
- multiple links can be a challange

`https://datapub.gfz.de/download/{ID}`:
- Need to find all files in registry and every sub-registry.
- Need to get file types.
    - Zip file type let currator decide action (lower confidence)
    - search for file type in file name if ZIP file (lower confidence) 
- Need to add up all file sizes.
    - inconsistent file sizes between found data and metadata let curator decide action (lower confidence)


